9.6.4 It is the responsibility of Party A to ensure that neither Party A nor Party A’s Affiliates engage in illegal or criminal activities, relying on their partnership with Didi;

9.6.5 Party A, Party A’s shareholders, legal representatives, Senior Management, or Party A’s Affiliates shall not make illegal profits, exploiting their relationship with the Didi staff (including, but not limited to, relatives, couples, friends);

9.6.6 Party A or Party A’s shareholders, legal representative, Senior Management, or Party A’s Affiliates shall comply with the provisions of the Trust and Integrity and Commercial Anti-Bribery Agreement between the Parties;

9.6.7 Party A shall not charge any fees against the Driver Users in the name of Didi;

9.6.8 Party A shall not compel the Driver Users to transact any business unrelated to Didi, or require the Driver Users to have unreasonable consumption, which may cause material adverse effects to Didi or cause adverse social effects (including but not limited to collective complaints, illegal assembly, petitions, marches, sit-ins, or confinement of Didi by Driver Users, news media releases);

9.6.9 Party A shall ensure that its staff and Affiliates adhere to Article 7 and shall not disclose Party B’s confidential information to third parties in any form;

9.6.10 In light of the fact that Didi may share relevant trade secrets with Party A during cooperation, Party A or any affiliate shall not cooperate with any entity competing with Didi (including but not limited to Meituan, CAR, Yongche, izu, Caocao, Dida) without prior written consent from Didi;

9.6.11 Party A shall not introduce Driver Users to entities competing with Didi (including but not limited to Meituan, CAR, Yongche, izu, Caocao, Dida), nor induce them to engage in activities that directly compete or conflict with Didi;

9.6.12 Party A shall refrain from instigating and organizing Driver Users to conduct illegal assemblies, petitions, marches, sit-ins, or confinement of Didi, etc., or any collective complaints, illegal assemblies, petitions, marches, sit-ins, or confinement of Didi by Driver Users that arise from the products or services provided by Party A;

9.6.13 Party A shall avoid disseminating information not published through Didi’s official channels, or disseminating rumors that may cause material adverse effects to Didi (including but not limited to collective complaints, illegal assemblies, petitions, marches, sit-ins, or confinement of Didi by Driver Users, and News media releases);

9.6.14 Party A shall refrain from maliciously slandering other companies, or taking measures to disrupt the market order, and engaging in unfair competition.
